p his life intact despite health concerns; Jackie, a young African-American woman diligently attending school after work; and Cindy, whose matter-of-fact attitude helps Deepak adapt to his job and his new life.   How May I Help You? is an incisive take on life in the United States and a reminder that the stories of low-wage employees can bring candor and humanity to debates about work, race, and immigration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 20. Sep 2019) 0aForeign workerszUnited States. 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aImmigrantszUnited StatesxEconomic conditions. 0aWorking poorzUnited States. 70(DE-601)1046171870(DE-588)4002805-7aArbeitswelt2gnd 70(DE-601)1554803750(DE-588)4344449-0aIndischer Einwanderer2gnd 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Social Classes & Economic Disparity.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311063539308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook-Package 2017z978311066755408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018z978311065859040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966475423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520966475.jpg  a978-3-11-063539-3  UC Press eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-065859-0  UCal Press eBook Package Frontlist 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066755-4  UC Press eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles